eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

actionOption.title: Action Option
actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

readonlyValue.title: Readonly Value
readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

byArtist.title: By Artist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

season.title: Season
season.description: A season in a media series.

bloodSupply.title: Blood Supply
bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

healthPlanNetworkId.title: Health Plan Network
healthPlanNetworkId.description: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

skills.title: Skills
skills.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

xpath.title: Xpath
xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

availability.title: Availability
availability.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

enginePower.title: Engine Power
enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.
    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 3: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

fuelCapacity.title: Fuel Capacity
fuelCapacity.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

increasesRiskOf.title: Increases Risk Of
increasesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

typeOfBed.title: Type Of Bed
typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

suggestedMinAge.title: Suggested Min Age
suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

inverseOf.title: Inverse Of
inverseOf.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

activityFrequency.title: Activity Frequency
activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

playerType.title: Player Type
playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

broadcastSubChannel.title: Broadcast Sub Channel
broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

contentType.title: Content Type
contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

preOp.title: Pre Op
preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

license.title: License
license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

itemCondition.title: Item Condition
itemCondition.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

customer.title: Customer
customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

wheelbase.title: Wheelbase
wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet

carbohydrateContent.title: Carbohydrate Content
carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

paymentDue.title: Payment Due
paymentDue.description: The date that payment is due.

tourBookingPage.title: Tour Booking Page
tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

colorist.title: Colorist
colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

procedureType.title: Procedure Type
procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

checkoutPageURLTemplate.title: Checkout Page Url Template
checkoutPageURLTemplate.description: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

connectedTo.title: Connected To
connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.title: Has Energy Efficiency Category
hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

citation.title: Citation
citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

suitableForDiet.title: Suitable For Diet
suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

accessibilitySummary.title: Accessibility Summary
accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

childTaxon.title: Child Taxon
childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

yearlyRevenue.title: Yearly Revenue
yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

associatedArticle.title: Associated Article
associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

scheduleTimezone.title: Schedule Timezone
scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

dropoffLocation.title: Dropoff Location
dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

knows.title: Knows
knows.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

broadcastAffiliateOf.title: Broadcast Affiliate Of
broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

superEvent.title: Super Event
superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

relatedDrug.title: Related Drug
relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

replyToUrl.title: Reply To Url
replyToUrl.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

providesBroadcastService.title: Provides Broadcast Service
providesBroadcastService.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

vehicleIdentificationNumber.title: Vehicle Identification Number
vehicleIdentificationNumber.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

handlingTime.title: Handling Time
handlingTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

sameAs.title: Same As
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

doesNotShip.title: Does Not Ship
doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

energyEfficiencyScaleMin.title: Energy Efficiency Scale Min
energyEfficiencyScaleMin.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

worksFor.title: Works For
worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.

restockingFee.title: Restocking Fee
restockingFee.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

geoWithin.title: Geo Within
geoWithin.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

physicalRequirement.title: Physical Requirement
physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

gameServer.title: Game Server
gameServer.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

financialAidEligible.title: Financial Aid Eligible
financialAidEligible.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

award.title: Award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

equal.title: Equal
equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

cvdFacilityId.title: Cvd Facility
cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

eventSchedule.title: Event Schedule
eventSchedule.description:
Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of
      repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly
      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that
      is associated with a [[Schedule]] using this property should not have [[startDate]] or [[endDate]] properties. These are instead defined within the associated
      [[Schedule]], this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months
      or seasons.

webCheckinTime.title: Web Checkin Time
webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

streetAddress.title: Street Address
streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

sportsTeam.title: Sports Team
sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

clipNumber.title: Clip Number
clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

broadcaster.title: Broadcaster
broadcaster.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

partOfSystem.title: Part Of System
partOfSystem.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

articleBody.title: Article Body
articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

contactlessPayment.title: Contactless Payment
contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

fatContent.title: Fat Content
fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

acceptedOffer.title: Accepted Offer
acceptedOffer.description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

includedDataCatalog.title: Included Data Catalog
includedDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

labelDetails.title: Label Details
labelDetails.description: Link to the drug's label details.

subtitleLanguage.title: Subtitle Language
subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

variesBy.title: Varies By
variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

gameLocation.title: Game Location
gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

measurementTechnique.title: Measurement Technique
measurementTechnique.description:
A technique or technology used in a [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]),
corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using [[variableMeasured]]). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.

For example, if [[variableMeasured]] is: molecule concentration, [[measurementTechnique]] could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".

If the [[variableMeasured]] is "depression rating", the [[measurementTechnique]] could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".

If there are several [[variableMeasured]] properties recorded for some given data object, use a [[PropertyValue]] for each [[variableMeasured]] and attach the corresponding [[measurementTechnique]].

healthPlanCostSharing.title: Health Plan Cost Sharing
healthPlanCostSharing.description: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

bed.title: Bed
bed.description:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

inPlaylist.title: In Playlist
inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

givenName.title: Given Name
givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

actionStatus.title: Action Status
actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

workLocation.title: Work Location
workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

arrivalAirport.title: Arrival Airport
arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

checkoutTime.title: Checkout Time
checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

price.title: Price
price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
* Note that both [RDFa](http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml-rdfa-primer/#using-the-content-attribute) and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.

validUntil.title: Valid Until
validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

contactPoints.title: Contact Points
contactPoints.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

agent.title: Agent
agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

doseSchedule.title: Dose Schedule
doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

reviewAspect.title: Review Aspect
reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

authenticator.title: Authenticator
authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

lesser.title: Lesser
lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

experienceRequirements.title: Experience Requirements
experienceRequirements.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

partOfEpisode.title: Part Of Episode
partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

targetUrl.title: Target Url
targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

diversityStaffingReport.title: Diversity Staffing Report
diversityStaffingReport.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

cvdNumC19HospPats.title: Cvd Num C19 Hosp Pats
cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

containsPlace.title: Contains Place
containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

qualifications.title: Qualifications
qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

validFor.title: Valid For
validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

specialCommitments.title: Special Commitments
specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

commentCount.title: Comment Count
commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

servicePostalAddress.title: Service Postal Address
servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

cookTime.title: Cook Time
cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

foundingDate.title: Founding Date
foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

taxonomicRange.title: Taxonomic Range
taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

resultReview.title: Result Review
resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

phoneticText.title: Phonetic Text
phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

repetitions.title: Repetitions
repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

reviewedBy.title: Reviewed By
reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

jobTitle.title: Job Title
jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

hostingOrganization.title: Hosting Organization
hostingOrganization.description: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

hasVariant.title: Has Variant
hasVariant.description: Indicates a [[Product]] that is a member of this [[ProductGroup]] (or [[ProductModel]]).

isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.title: Is Located In Subcellular Location
isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.description: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

temporalCoverage.title: Temporal Coverage
temporalCoverage.description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In
      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.
      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

dateCreated.title: Date Created
dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

deliveryMethod.title: Delivery Method
deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

owns.title: Owns
owns.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

discussionUrl.title: Discussion Url
discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

duplicateTherapy.title: Duplicate Therapy
duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

numberOfBathroomsTotal.title: Number Of Bathrooms Total
numberOfBathroomsTotal.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

drugUnit.title: Drug Unit
drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

dietFeatures.title: Diet Features
dietFeatures.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

free.title: Free
free.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

copyrightNotice.title: Copyright Notice
copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

learningResourceType.title: Learning Resource Type
learningResourceType.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

estimatedFlightDuration.title: Estimated Flight Duration
estimatedFlightDuration.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

requiredMinAge.title: Required Min Age
requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

borrower.title: Borrower
borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

billingPeriod.title: Billing Period
billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

awards.title: Awards
awards.description: Awards won by or for this item.

differentialDiagnosis.title: Differential Diagnosis
differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

loanTerm.title: Loan Term
loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

accessModeSufficient.title: Access Mode Sufficient
accessModeSufficient.description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessModeSufficient-vocabulary).

maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.title: Maximum Virtual Attendee Capacity
maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

byMonthWeek.title: By Month Week
byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

pathophysiology.title: Pathophysiology
pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

guidelineSubject.title: Guideline Subject
guidelineSubject.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

dissolutionDate.title: Dissolution Date
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

conditionsOfAccess.title: Conditions Of Access
conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

administrationRoute.title: Administration Route
administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

paymentMethodId.title: Payment Method
paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

dateReceived.title: Date Received
dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

healthPlanId.title: Health Plan
healthPlanId.description: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)

interactivityType.title: Interactivity Type
interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

lodgingUnitType.title: Lodging Unit Type
lodgingUnitType.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

medicalSpecialty.title: Medical Specialty
medicalSpecialty.description: A medical specialty of the provider.

returnPolicyCategory.title: Return Policy Category
returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

device.title: Device
device.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

availableChannel.title: Available Channel
availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

abstract.title: Abstract
abstract.description: An abstract is a short description that summarizes a [[CreativeWork]].

cholesterolContent.title: Cholesterol Content
cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

numChildren.title: Num Children
numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

membershipNumber.title: Membership Number
membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

distribution.title: Distribution
distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

valueMinLength.title: Value Min Length
valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

guidelineDate.title: Guideline Date
guidelineDate.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

programMembershipUsed.title: Program Membership Used
programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

medicineSystem.title: Medicine System
medicineSystem.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

fileFormat.title: File Format
fileFormat.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content, e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

interpretedAsClaim.title: Interpreted As Claim
interpretedAsClaim.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

serviceOperator.title: Service Operator
serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

broadcastOfEvent.title: Broadcast Of Event
broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

bookingAgent.title: Booking Agent
bookingAgent.description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

itemReviewed.title: Item Reviewed
itemReviewed.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

returnLabelSource.title: Return Label Source
returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

vehicleInteriorType.title: Vehicle Interior Type
vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

originatesFrom.title: Originates From
originatesFrom.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

interactionType.title: Interaction Type
interactionType.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

hasMap.title: Has Map
hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

safetyConsideration.title: Safety Consideration
safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

vehicleEngine.title: Vehicle Engine
vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

text.title: Text
text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

fundedItem.title: Funded Item
fundedItem.description: Indicates something directly or indirectly funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]]. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

archivedAt.title: Archived At
archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

molecularWeight.title: Molecular Weight
molecularWeight.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

gtin.title: Gtin
gtin.description:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

The GS1 [digital link specifications](https://www.gs1.org/standards/Digital-Link/) express GTINs as URLs (URIs, IRIs, etc.). Details including regular expression examples can be found in, Section 6 of the GS1 URI Syntax specification; see also [schema.org tracking issue](https://github.com/schemaorg/schemaorg/issues/3156#issuecomment-1209522809) for schema.org-specific discussion. A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also [GS1's GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) and [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Trade_Item_Number) for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged. The [[gtin]] property generalizes the earlier [[gtin8]], [[gtin12]], [[gtin13]], and [[gtin14]] properties.

Note also that this is a definition for how to include GTINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of GTINs in general - see the GS1 documentation for authoritative details.

jobStartDate.title: Job Start Date
jobStartDate.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

iataCode.title: Iata Code
iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

contactType.title: Contact Type
contactType.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

characterName.title: Character Name
characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

dateDeleted.title: Date Deleted
dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

isRelatedTo.title: Is Related To
isRelatedTo.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

negativeNotes.title: Negative Notes
negativeNotes.description:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[negativeNotes]] can be used on [[Product]].

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most negative is at the beginning of the list).

alternativeHeadline.title: Alternative Headline
alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

assembly.title: Assembly
assembly.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

application.title: Application
application.description: An application that can complete the request.

creditText.title: Credit Text
creditText.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

suggestedMeasurement.title: Suggested Measurement
suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

eventStatus.title: Event Status
eventStatus.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

containedIn.title: Contained In
containedIn.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

bankAccountType.title: Bank Account Type
bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

trailer.title: Trailer
trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

documentation.title: Documentation
documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

bioChemInteraction.title: Bio Chem Interaction
bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

naturalProgression.title: Natural Progression
naturalProgression.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

paymentStatus.title: Payment Status
paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

itemOffered.title: Item Offered
itemOffered.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

gameEdition.title: Game Edition
gameEdition.description: The edition of a video game.

numberOfBedrooms.title: Number Of Bedrooms
numberOfBedrooms.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

intensity.title: Intensity
intensity.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

funding.title: Funding
funding.description: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

proprietaryName.title: Proprietary Name
proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

sharedContent.title: Shared Content
sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

collection.title: Collection
collection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

interactionStatistic.title: Interaction Statistic
interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

isPartOfBioChemEntity.title: Is Part Of Bio Chem Entity
isPartOfBioChemEntity.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

greaterOrEqual.title: Greater Or Equal
greaterOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

events.title: Events
events.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

numberOfDoors.title: Number Of Doors
numberOfDoors.description: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

lastReviewed.title: Last Reviewed
lastReviewed.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

foodEvent.title: Food Event
foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

workExample.title: Work Example
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

workPerformed.title: Work Performed
workPerformed.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

identifyingExam.title: Identifying Exam
identifyingExam.description: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

includedInDataCatalog.title: Included In Data Catalog
includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

currentExchangeRate.title: Current Exchange Rate
currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

dependencies.title: Dependencies
dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

duration.title: Duration
duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

jobLocation.title: Job Location
jobLocation.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

volumeNumber.title: Volume Number
volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

torque.title: Torque
torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

publishedOn.title: Published On
publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

algorithm.title: Algorithm
algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

legislationLegalValue.title: Legislation Legal Value
legislationLegalValue.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

associatedClaimReview.title: Associated Claim Review
associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

answerExplanation.title: Answer Explanation
answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

seeks.title: Seeks
seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

diagnosis.title: Diagnosis
diagnosis.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

mobileUrl.title: Mobile Url
mobileUrl.description:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing environments. Pages and sites referenced with the long-established [[url]] property should ideally also be usable on a wide variety of devices, including mobile phones. In most cases, it would be pointless and counter productive to attempt to update all [[url]] markup to use [[mobileUrl]] for more mobile-oriented pages. The property is intended for the case when items (primarily [[Product]] and [[Offer]]) have extra URLs hosted on an additional "mobile site" alongside the main one. It should not be taken as an endorsement of this publication style.

requiredQuantity.title: Required Quantity
requiredQuantity.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

about.title: About
about.description: The subject matter of the content.

hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.title: Has Energy Consumption Details
hasEnergyConsumptionDetails.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

expressedIn.title: Expressed In
expressedIn.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

weight.title: Weight
weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

composer.title: Composer
composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

clinicalPharmacology.title: Clinical Pharmacology
clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

postalCodePrefix.title: Postal Code Prefix
postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

shippingDetails.title: Shipping Details
shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

arrivalStation.title: Arrival Station
arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

unnamedSourcesPolicy.title: Unnamed Sources Policy
unnamedSourcesPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

educationRequirements.title: Education Requirements
educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

salaryUponCompletion.title: Salary Upon Completion
salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

claimInterpreter.title: Claim Interpreter
claimInterpreter.description:
For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content
    sed to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

vehicleInteriorColor.title: Vehicle Interior Color
vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

affectedBy.title: Affected By
affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

realEstateAgent.title: Real Estate Agent
realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

subOrganization.title: Sub Organization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

issueNumber.title: Issue Number
issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

encodings.title: Encodings
encodings.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

recipient.title: Recipient
recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

musicCompositionForm.title: Music Composition Form
musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

fileSize.title: File Size
fileSize.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

foundingLocation.title: Founding Location
foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

departureBoatTerminal.title: Departure Boat Terminal
departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

requiresSubscription.title: Requires Subscription
requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

tool.title: Tool
tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.title: Number Of Available Accommodation Units
numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

funder.title: Funder
funder.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

geoOverlaps.title: Geo Overlaps
geoOverlaps.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

iso6523Code.title: Iso6523 Code
iso6523Code.description: An organization identifier as defined in ISO 6523(-1). Note that many existing organization identifiers such as [leiCode](https://schema.org/leiCode), [duns](https://schema.org/duns) and [vatID](https://schema.org/vatID) can be expressed as an ISO 6523 identifier by setting the ICD part of the ISO 6523 identifier accordingly.

prescriptionStatus.title: Prescription Status
prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

accommodationCategory.title: Accommodation Category
accommodationCategory.description: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions, e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields  for suggested values).

hasCourse.title: Has Course
hasCourse.description: A course or class that is one of the learning opportunities that constitute an educational / occupational program. No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

bioChemSimilarity.title: Bio Chem Similarity
bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

diversityPolicy.title: Diversity Policy
diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

drug.title: Drug
drug.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

hasMerchantReturnPolicy.title: Has Merchant Return Policy
hasMerchantReturnPolicy.description: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

cvdCollectionDate.title: Cvd Collection Date
cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

lesserOrEqual.title: Lesser Or Equal
lesserOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

videoFormat.title: Video Format
videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

recordLabel.title: Record Label
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

associatedPathophysiology.title: Associated Pathophysiology
associatedPathophysiology.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

isPartOf.title: Is Part Of
isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

geoEquals.title: Geo Equals
geoEquals.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

sportsEvent.title: Sports Event
sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

providesService.title: Provides Service
providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

prescribingInfo.title: Prescribing Info
prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

pregnancyWarning.title: Pregnancy Warning
pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

businessFunction.title: Business Function
businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

instrument.title: Instrument
instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

pattern.title: Pattern
pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

verificationFactCheckingPolicy.title: Verification Fact Checking Policy
verificationFactCheckingPolicy.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.title: Monthly Minimum Repayment Amount
monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

offersPrescriptionByMail.title: Offers Prescription By Mail
offersPrescriptionByMail.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

touristType.title: Tourist Type
touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

editor.title: Editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

governmentBenefitsInfo.title: Government Benefits Info
governmentBenefitsInfo.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

unitCode.title: Unit Code
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

countriesNotSupported.title: Countries Not Supported
countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

dateModified.title: Date Modified
dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

translationOfWork.title: Translation Of Work
translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g. 物种起源 is a translationOf “On the Origin of Species”.

legalStatus.title: Legal Status
legalStatus.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

printColumn.title: Print Column
printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

occupancy.title: Occupancy
occupancy.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

billingDuration.title: Billing Duration
billingDuration.description: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

hasRepresentation.title: Has Representation
hasRepresentation.description: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

creativeWorkStatus.title: Creative Work Status
creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

isBasedOnUrl.title: Is Based On Url
isBasedOnUrl.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

eligibilityToWorkRequirement.title: Eligibility To Work Requirement
eligibilityToWorkRequirement.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

isFamilyFriendly.title: Is Family Friendly
isFamilyFriendly.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

blogPosts.title: Blog Posts
blogPosts.description: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

hasBioPolymerSequence.title: Has Bio Polymer Sequence
hasBioPolymerSequence.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEntity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

addressCountry.title: Address Country
addressCountry.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1).

tissueSample.title: Tissue Sample
tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

infectiousAgent.title: Infectious Agent
infectiousAgent.description: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

driveWheelConfiguration.title: Drive Wheel Configuration
driveWheelConfiguration.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

leaseLength.title: Lease Length
leaseLength.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

gtin12.title: Gtin12
gtin12.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

operatingSystem.title: Operating System
operatingSystem.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

sizeSystem.title: Size System
sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

estimatedSalary.title: Estimated Salary
estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

numberOfAccommodationUnits.title: Number Of Accommodation Units
numberOfAccommodationUnits.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

landlord.title: Landlord
landlord.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

featureList.title: Feature List
featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

openingHours.title: Opening Hours
openingHours.description: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

maps.title: Maps
maps.description: A URL to a map of the place.

serviceAudience.title: Service Audience
serviceAudience.description: The audience eligible for this service.

isAccessibleForFree.title: Is Accessible For Free
isAccessibleForFree.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

isSimilarTo.title: Is Similar To
isSimilarTo.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

cvdNumTotBeds.title: Cvd Num Tot Beds
cvdNumTotBeds.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

ticketToken.title: Ticket Token
ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

expectedArrivalFrom.title: Expected Arrival From
expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

diet.title: Diet
diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

numberOfLoanPayments.title: Number Of Loan Payments
numberOfLoanPayments.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

broadcastTimezone.title: Broadcast Timezone
broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

relatedLink.title: Related Link
relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

author.title: Author
author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

ratingExplanation.title: Rating Explanation
ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

additionalName.title: Additional Name
additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

starRating.title: Star Rating
starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

secondaryPrevention.title: Secondary Prevention
secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

regionsAllowed.title: Regions Allowed
regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

educationalCredentialAwarded.title: Educational Credential Awarded
educationalCredentialAwarded.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

infectiousAgentClass.title: Infectious Agent Class
infectiousAgentClass.description: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

printEdition.title: Print Edition
printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

contentUrl.title: Content Url
contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

step.title: Step
step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

validIn.title: Valid In
validIn.description: The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

artMedium.title: Art Medium
artMedium.description: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

numberOfAxles.title: Number Of Axles
numberOfAxles.description: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

loanPaymentFrequency.title: Loan Payment Frequency
loanPaymentFrequency.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

unsaturatedFatContent.title: Unsaturated Fat Content
unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

typicalCreditsPerTerm.title: Typical Credits Per Term
typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

applicableCountry.title: Applicable Country
applicableCountry.description: A country where a particular merchant return policy applies to, for example the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

scheduledTime.title: Scheduled Time
scheduledTime.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

object.title: Object
object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

contentReferenceTime.title: Content Reference Time
contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

sizeGroup.title: Size Group
sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular"

biologicalRole.title: Biological Role
biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

event.title: Event
event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

duns.title: Duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

performerIn.title: Performer In
performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

inChIKey.title: In Ch I Key
inChIKey.description: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

carrier.title: Carrier
carrier.description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

correction.title: Correction
correction.description: Indicates a correction to a [[CreativeWork]], either via a [[CorrectionComment]], textually or in another document.

iupacName.title: Iupac Name
iupacName.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

returnMethod.title: Return Method
returnMethod.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

supplyTo.title: Supply To
supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

sdDatePublished.title: Sd Date Published
sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]]

suggestedGender.title: Suggested Gender
suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

ethicsPolicy.title: Ethics Policy
ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

adverseOutcome.title: Adverse Outcome
adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or otherwise life-threatening or requiring immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriousAdverseOutcome instead.

molecularFormula.title: Molecular Formula
molecularFormula.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

populationType.title: Population Type
populationType.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]].

leiCode.title: Lei Code
leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

error.title: Error
error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

transmissionMethod.title: Transmission Method
transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

postalCodeRange.title: Postal Code Range
postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

sugarContent.title: Sugar Content
sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

breadcrumb.title: Breadcrumb
breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

priceComponent.title: Price Component
priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

quarantineGuidelines.title: Quarantine Guidelines
quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

travelBans.title: Travel Bans
travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

target.title: Target
target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

validThrough.title: Valid Through
validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

productID.title: Product
productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

productionCompany.title: Production Company
productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

countryOfOrigin.title: Country Of Origin
countryOfOrigin.description:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product. The exact interpretation of this may vary by context and product type, and cannot be fully enumerated here.

subEvent.title: Sub Event
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

activityDuration.title: Activity Duration
activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

vatID.title: Vat
vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

engineType.title: Engine Type
engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

cvdFacilityCounty.title: Cvd Facility County
cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

vehicleSeatingCapacity.title: Vehicle Seating Capacity
vehicleSeatingCapacity.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

hasDefinedTerm.title: Has Defined Term
hasDefinedTerm.description: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

valueName.title: Value Name
valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

credentialCategory.title: Credential Category
credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

overdosage.title: Overdosage
overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

serviceSmsNumber.title: Service Sms Number
serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

procedure.title: Procedure
procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

webFeed.title: Web Feed
webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

partOfInvoice.title: Part Of Invoice
partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

availableService.title: Available Service
availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

availableTest.title: Available Test
availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

applicationSuite.title: Application Suite
applicationSuite.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

hasAdultConsideration.title: Has Adult Consideration
hasAdultConsideration.description: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

encodesCreativeWork.title: Encodes Creative Work
