encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

timeRequired.title: Time Required
timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'PT30M', 'PT1H25M'.

signOrSymptom.title: Sign Or Symptom
signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

significantLinks.title: Significant Links
significantLinks.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

broadcastFrequencyValue.title: Broadcast Frequency Value
broadcastFrequencyValue.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

costOrigin.title: Cost Origin
costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

episodes.title: Episodes
episodes.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

numberOfPreviousOwners.title: Number Of Previous Owners
numberOfPreviousOwners.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

requiredMaxAge.title: Required Max Age
requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

subStageSuffix.title: Sub Stage Suffix
subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

significance.title: Significance
significance.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

numConstraints.title: Num Constraints
numConstraints.description: Indicates the number of constraints (not counting [[populationType]]) defined for a particular [[StatisticalPopulation]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalPopulation]].

partOfSeason.title: Part Of Season
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

knowsLanguage.title: Knows Language
knowsLanguage.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

typicalAgeRange.title: Typical Age Range
typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

recommendationStrength.title: Recommendation Strength
recommendationStrength.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

cvdNumC19Died.title: Cvd Num C19 Died
cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

totalPrice.title: Total Price
totalPrice.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

businessDays.title: Business Days
businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

catalogNumber.title: Catalog Number
catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

alignmentType.title: Alignment Type
alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

containedInPlace.title: Contained In Place
containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

genre.title: Genre
genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

itemListOrder.title: Item List Order
itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

returnShippingFeesAmount.title: Return Shipping Fees Amount
returnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

targetCollection.title: Target Collection
targetCollection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.title: Is Involved In Biological Process
isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

maximumEnrollment.title: Maximum Enrollment
maximumEnrollment.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

trainName.title: Train Name
trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

utterances.title: Utterances
utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

suggestedAnswer.title: Suggested Answer
suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

purchaseDate.title: Purchase Date
purchaseDate.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

reservedTicket.title: Reserved Ticket
reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

httpMethod.title: Http Method
httpMethod.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

producer.title: Producer
producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

targetPopulation.title: Target Population
targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

programType.title: Program Type
programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

coverageStartTime.title: Coverage Start Time
coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

bodyType.title: Body Type
bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

musicGroupMember.title: Music Group Member
musicGroupMember.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

workPresented.title: Work Presented
workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

associatedDisease.title: Associated Disease
associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

applicationSubCategory.title: Application Sub Category
applicationSubCategory.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

includesObject.title: Includes Object
includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

schemaVersion.title: Schema Version
schemaVersion.description:
Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to
    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explored in the community.

audience.title: Audience
audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

parentItem.title: Parent Item
parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

gamePlatform.title: Game Platform
gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

courseCode.title: Course Code
courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

functionalClass.title: Functional Class
functionalClass.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

encoding.title: Encoding
encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

ingredients.title: Ingredients
ingredients.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

correctionsPolicy.title: Corrections Policy
correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

publisherImprint.title: Publisher Imprint
publisherImprint.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

attendee.title: Attendee
attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

possibleTreatment.title: Possible Treatment
possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

normalRange.title: Normal Range
normalRange.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

departureAirport.title: Departure Airport
departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

bodyLocation.title: Body Location
bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

messageAttachment.title: Message Attachment
messageAttachment.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.title: Item Defect Return Shipping Fees Amount
itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

duringMedia.title: During Media
duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

namedPosition.title: Named Position
namedPosition.description: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

maxValue.title: Max Value
maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

geoCrosses.title: Geo Crosses
geoCrosses.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

passengerPriorityStatus.title: Passenger Priority Status
passengerPriorityStatus.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

numberOfPlayers.title: Number Of Players
numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

biomechnicalClass.title: Biomechnical Class
biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

reservationId.title: Reservation
reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

signDetected.title: Sign Detected
signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

doseValue.title: Dose Value
doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

description.@value: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

acrissCode.title: Acriss Code
acrissCode.description: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

appearance.title: Appearance
appearance.description: Indicates an occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

answerCount.title: Answer Count
answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

transFatContent.title: Trans Fat Content
transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

interactionService.title: Interaction Service
interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

beneficiaryBank.title: Beneficiary Bank
beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

accessibilityAPI.title: Accessibility Api
accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityAPI-vocabulary).

sdPublisher.title: Sd Publisher
sdPublisher.description:
Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The
[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

fuelType.title: Fuel Type
fuelType.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

acceptsReservations.title: Accepts Reservations
acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

startOffset.title: Start Offset
startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

eligibleRegion.title: Eligible Region
eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

countryOfLastProcessing.title: Country Of Last Processing
countryOfLastProcessing.description: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

codeSampleType.title: Code Sample Type
codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

seasons.title: Seasons
seasons.description: A season in a media series.

opens.title: Opens
opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

rangeIncludes.title: Range Includes
rangeIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

returnPolicySeasonalOverride.title: Return Policy Seasonal Override
returnPolicySeasonalOverride.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

providerMobility.title: Provider Mobility
providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

honorificPrefix.title: Honorific Prefix
honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

ccRecipient.title: Cc Recipient
ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.title: Customer Remorse Return Shipping Fees Amount
customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

measuredProperty.title: Measured Property
measuredProperty.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], either a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

arrivalBusStop.title: Arrival Bus Stop
arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

recipeCuisine.title: Recipe Cuisine
recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

bestRating.title: Best Rating
bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

releaseNotes.title: Release Notes
releaseNotes.description: Description of what changed in this version.

sensoryRequirement.title: Sensory Requirement
sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

asin.title: Asin
asin.description:
An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).

Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
ASINs are most commonly encoded as text strings, but the [asin] property supports URL/URI as potential values too.

evidenceOrigin.title: Evidence Origin
evidenceOrigin.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

programPrerequisites.title: Program Prerequisites
programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

chemicalComposition.title: Chemical Composition
chemicalComposition.description: The chemical composition describes the identity and relative ratio of the chemical elements that make up the substance.

countriesSupported.title: Countries Supported
countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

hoursAvailable.title: Hours Available
hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

availableOnDevice.title: Available On Device
availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

stageAsNumber.title: Stage As Number
stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

familyName.title: Family Name
familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

deliveryTime.title: Delivery Time
deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

isProprietary.title: Is Proprietary
isProprietary.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

gameItem.title: Game Item
gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

proteinContent.title: Protein Content
proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

bccRecipient.title: Bcc Recipient
bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

winner.title: Winner
winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

freeShippingThreshold.title: Free Shipping Threshold
freeShippingThreshold.description: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

accessibilityFeature.title: Accessibility Feature
accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityFeature-vocabulary).

hasCredential.title: Has Credential
hasCredential.description: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

study.title: Study
study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

screenCount.title: Screen Count
screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

gtin8.title: Gtin8
gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

embeddedTextCaption.title: Embedded Text Caption
embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

offerCount.title: Offer Count
offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

spatialCoverage.title: Spatial Coverage
spatialCoverage.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

shippingOrigin.title: Shipping Origin
shippingOrigin.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

question.title: Question
question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

exercisePlan.title: Exercise Plan
exercisePlan.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

reservationFor.title: Reservation For
reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

sensoryUnit.title: Sensory Unit
sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

healthPlanMarketingUrl.title: Health Plan Marketing Url
healthPlanMarketingUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the plan brochure for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

geoMidpoint.title: Geo Midpoint
geoMidpoint.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

maxPrice.title: Max Price
maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

speed.title: Speed
speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.

geo.title: Geo
geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

paymentMethod.title: Payment Method
paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

loanRepaymentForm.title: Loan Repayment Form
loanRepaymentForm.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

usedToDiagnose.title: Used To Diagnose
usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

blogPost.title: Blog Post
blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

unitText.title: Unit Text
unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

releaseDate.title: Release Date
releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

runtime.title: Runtime
runtime.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

monthsOfExperience.title: Months Of Experience
monthsOfExperience.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

jurisdiction.title: Jurisdiction
jurisdiction.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

brand.title: Brand
brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

rxcui.title: Rxcui
rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

saturatedFatContent.title: Saturated Fat Content
saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

followup.title: Followup
followup.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

endorsee.title: Endorsee
endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

employmentType.title: Employment Type
employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

numberOfItems.title: Number Of Items
numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

returnFees.title: Return Fees
returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

acquiredFrom.title: Acquired From
acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

openingHoursSpecification.title: Opening Hours Specification
openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

linkRelationship.title: Link Relationship
linkRelationship.description: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

accessMode.title: Access Mode
accessMode.description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessMode-vocabulary).

mealService.title: Meal Service
mealService.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

subEvents.title: Sub Events
subEvents.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

mileageFromOdometer.title: Mileage From Odometer
mileageFromOdometer.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

postalCodeEnd.title: Postal Code End
postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

recipe.title: Recipe
recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

surface.title: Surface
surface.description: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

urlTemplate.title: Url Template
urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

nonprofitStatus.title: Nonprofit Status
nonprofitStatus.description: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

broadcastServiceTier.title: Broadcast Service Tier
broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

issn.title: Issn
issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

hasOccupation.title: Has Occupation
hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

inChI.title: In Ch I
inChI.description: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

originalMediaContextDescription.title: Original Media Context Description
originalMediaContextDescription.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

exerciseType.title: Exercise Type
exerciseType.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

arrivalBoatTerminal.title: Arrival Boat Terminal
arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

editEIDR.title: Edit Eidr
editEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use [[titleEIDR]] alone (for a general description), or alongside [[editEIDR]] for a more edit-specific description.

uploadDate.title: Upload Date
uploadDate.description: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

executableLibraryName.title: Executable Library Name
executableLibraryName.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

printSection.title: Print Section
printSection.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

productionDate.title: Production Date
productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

numAdults.title: Num Adults
numAdults.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

numberOfBeds.title: Number Of Beds
numberOfBeds.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

readBy.title: Read By
readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

hasMolecularFunction.title: Has Molecular Function
hasMolecularFunction.description: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

geoDisjoint.title: Geo Disjoint
geoDisjoint.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

netWorth.title: Net Worth
netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

guideline.title: Guideline
guideline.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

byDay.title: By Day
byDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the week on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. May be specified using either [[DayOfWeek]], or alternatively [[Text]] conforming to iCal's syntax for byDay recurrence rules.

totalJobOpenings.title: Total Job Openings
totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

broadcastDisplayName.title: Broadcast Display Name
broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

accessCode.title: Access Code
accessCode.description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

estimatesRiskOf.title: Estimates Risk Of
estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

usageInfo.title: Usage Info
usageInfo.description:
The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.

This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

installUrl.title: Install Url
installUrl.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

knownVehicleDamages.title: Known Vehicle Damages
knownVehicleDamages.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

salaryCurrency.title: Salary Currency
salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

homeTeam.title: Home Team
homeTeam.description: The home team in a sports event.

byMonthDay.title: By Month Day
byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

isLiveBroadcast.title: Is Live Broadcast
isLiveBroadcast.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

repeatCount.title: Repeat Count
repeatCount.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

servingSize.title: Serving Size
servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

foodEstablishment.title: Food Establishment
foodEstablishment.description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

candidate.title: Candidate
candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

language.title: Language
language.description: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

petsAllowed.title: Pets Allowed
petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

appliesToDeliveryMethod.title: Applies To Delivery Method
appliesToDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

contactPoint.title: Contact Point
contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

alcoholWarning.title: Alcohol Warning
alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

relatedTherapy.title: Related Therapy
relatedTherapy.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

hasHealthAspect.title: Has Health Aspect
hasHealthAspect.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

educationalProgramMode.title: Educational Program Mode
educationalProgramMode.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

ineligibleRegion.title: Ineligible Region
ineligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

subStructure.title: Sub Structure
subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

position.title: Position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

encodingFormat.title: Encoding Format
encodingFormat.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

dateVehicleFirstRegistered.title: Date Vehicle First Registered
dateVehicleFirstRegistered.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

audienceType.title: Audience Type
audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

drugClass.title: Drug Class
drugClass.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

code.title: Code
code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

priceSpecification.title: Price Specification
priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

mainContentOfPage.title: Main Content Of Page
mainContentOfPage.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

copyrightYear.title: Copyright Year
copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

epidemiology.title: Epidemiology
epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

geoIntersects.title: Geo Intersects
geoIntersects.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

serviceLocation.title: Service Location
serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

recipeInstructions.title: Recipe Instructions
recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

coverageEndTime.title: Coverage End Time
coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

partOfSeries.title: Part Of Series
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

inProductGroupWithID.title: In Product Group With
inProductGroupWithID.description: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

valueMaxLength.title: Value Max Length
valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

serviceOutput.title: Service Output
serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

distance.title: Distance
distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

scheduledPaymentDate.title: Scheduled Payment Date
scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

dateRead.title: Date Read
dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

entertainmentBusiness.title: Entertainment Business
entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

inCodeSet.title: In Code Set
inCodeSet.description: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.

homeLocation.title: Home Location
homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

downvoteCount.title: Downvote Count
downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

weightTotal.title: Weight Total
weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

includedRiskFactor.title: Included Risk Factor
includedRiskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

recourseLoan.title: Recourse Loan
recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

applicationContact.title: Application Contact
applicationContact.description: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

isPlanForApartment.title: Is Plan For Apartment
isPlanForApartment.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

experienceInPlaceOfEducation.title: Experience In Place Of Education
experienceInPlaceOfEducation.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.title: Customer Remorse Return Label Source
customerRemorseReturnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

performTime.title: Perform Time
performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

performers.title: Performers
performers.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

costCategory.title: Cost Category
costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

transitTimeLabel.title: Transit Time Label
transitTimeLabel.description: Label to match an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with a [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] (within the context of a [[shippingSettingsLink]] cross-reference).

referencesOrder.title: References Order
referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

validFrom.title: Valid From
validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

latitude.title: Latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

valueRequired.title: Value Required
valueRequired.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

eligibleTransactionVolume.title: Eligible Transaction Volume
eligibleTransactionVolume.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

hasDigitalDocumentPermission.title: Has Digital Document Permission
hasDigitalDocumentPermission.description: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

mainEntity.title: Main Entity
mainEntity.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

referenceQuantity.title: Reference Quantity
referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

maximumAttendeeCapacity.title: Maximum Attendee Capacity
maximumAttendeeCapacity.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

dateSent.title: Date Sent
dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

creator.title: Creator
creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

speakable.title: Speakable
speakable.description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.

2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.

3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.


For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this
we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]]  which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

discountCode.title: Discount Code
discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

endOffset.title: End Offset
endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

cvdNumVent.title: Cvd Num Vent
cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

underName.title: Under Name
underName.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

loanMortgageMandateAmount.title: Loan Mortgage Mandate Amount
loanMortgageMandateAmount.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

durationOfWarranty.title: Duration Of Warranty
durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

ratingCount.title: Rating Count
ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

datePosted.title: Date Posted
datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

strengthUnit.title: Strength Unit
strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

gender.title: Gender
gender.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

produces.title: Produces
produces.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

drainsTo.title: Drains To
drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

hasOfferCatalog.title: Has Offer Catalog
hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

follows.title: Follows
follows.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

shippingRate.title: Shipping Rate
shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

healthPlanDrugTier.title: Health Plan Drug Tier
healthPlanDrugTier.description: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

backstory.title: Backstory
backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

supply.title: Supply
supply.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

ratingValue.title: Rating Value
ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

teaches.title: Teaches
teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

commentTime.title: Comment Time
commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

departureGate.title: Departure Gate
departureGate.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

orderDelivery.title: Order Delivery
orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

geographicArea.title: Geographic Area
geographicArea.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

representativeOfPage.title: Representative Of Page
representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

firstPerformance.title: First Performance
firstPerformance.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

healthPlanPharmacyCategory.title: Health Plan Pharmacy Category
healthPlanPharmacyCategory.description: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

numberOfAirbags.title: Number Of Airbags
numberOfAirbags.description: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

deliveryStatus.title: Delivery Status
deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

temporal.title: Temporal
temporal.description:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

size.title: Size
size.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

mpn.title: Mpn
mpn.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

menu.title: Menu
menu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

cssSelector.title: Css Selector
cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

antagonist.title: Antagonist
antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

exchangeRateSpread.title: Exchange Rate Spread
exchangeRateSpread.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

bookingTime.title: Booking Time
bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

lowPrice.title: Low Price
lowPrice.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

totalTime.title: Total Time
totalTime.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

typeOfGood.title: Type Of Good
typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

cvdNumICUBeds.title: Cvd Num Icu Beds
cvdNumICUBeds.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

translator.title: Translator
translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

category.title: Category
category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

merchantReturnLink.title: Merchant Return Link
merchantReturnLink.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

broadcastFrequency.title: Broadcast Frequency
broadcastFrequency.description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequences of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

issuedThrough.title: Issued Through
issuedThrough.description: The service through which the permit was granted.

stepValue.title: Step Value
stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

creditedTo.title: Credited To
creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

permittedUsage.title: Permitted Usage
permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

aggregateRating.title: Aggregate Rating
aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

preparation.title: Preparation
preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

cvdNumC19OverflowPats.title: Cvd Num C19 Overflow Pats
cvdNumC19OverflowPats.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

successorOf.title: Successor Of
successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

cvdNumC19HOPats.title: Cvd Num C19 Ho Pats
cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

userInteractionCount.title: User Interaction Count
userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

birthPlace.title: Birth Place
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

trackingUrl.title: Tracking Url
trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

disambiguatingDescription.title: Disambiguating Description
disambiguatingDescription.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

nonEqual.title: Non Equal
nonEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

offeredBy.title: Offered By
offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

termCode.title: Term Code
termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]]

billingAddress.title: Billing Address
billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

fuelEfficiency.title: Fuel Efficiency
fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

encodesBioChemEntity.title: Encodes Bio Chem Entity
encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

line.title: Line
line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

departureTerminal.title: Departure Terminal
departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

dayOfWeek.title: Day Of Week
dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

upvoteCount.title: Upvote Count
upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

map.title: Map
map.description: A URL to a map of the place.

byMonth.title: By Month
byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

geoRadius.title: Geo Radius
geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

announcementLocation.title: Announcement Location
announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

accountablePerson.title: Accountable Person
accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

downPayment.title: Down Payment
downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

worstRating.title: Worst Rating
worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

discusses.title: Discusses
discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

vehicleModelDate.title: Vehicle Model Date
vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

associatedAnatomy.title: Associated Anatomy
associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

accessibilityHazard.title: Accessibility Hazard
accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).

legislationDateVersion.title: Legislation Date Version
legislationDateVersion.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g.: when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

checkinTime.title: Checkin Time
checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

comprisedOf.title: Comprised Of
comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

doseUnit.title: Dose Unit
doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

artform.title: Artform
artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

warrantyPromise.title: Warranty Promise
warrantyPromise.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

lodgingUnitDescription.title: Lodging Unit Description
lodgingUnitDescription.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

costCurrency.title: Cost Currency
costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter) of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

episode.title: Episode
episode.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

feesAndCommissionsSpecification.title: Fees And Commissions Specification
feesAndCommissionsSpecification.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

seatRow.title: Seat Row
seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

contentRating.title: Content Rating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

possibleComplication.title: Possible Complication
possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

isrcCode.title: Isrc Code
isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

jobBenefits.title: Job Benefits
jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

branchCode.title: Branch Code
branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

sampleType.title: Sample Type
sampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

tocContinuation.title: Toc Continuation
tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

paymentUrl.title: Payment Url
paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

applicantLocationRequirements.title: Applicant Location Requirements
applicantLocationRequirements.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

recordedAt.title: Recorded At
recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

processorRequirements.title: Processor Requirements
processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

itemDefectReturnFees.title: Item Defect Return Fees
itemDefectReturnFees.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

publication.title: Publication
publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

physiologicalBenefits.title: Physiological Benefits
physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

sdLicense.title: Sd License
sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

printPage.title: Print Page
printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.title: Maximum Physical Attendee Capacity
maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

numberOfPartialBathrooms.title: Number Of Partial Bathrooms
numberOfPartialBathrooms.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

reservationStatus.title: Reservation Status
reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

runsTo.title: Runs To
runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

subTrip.title: Sub Trip
subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

carrierRequirements.title: Carrier Requirements
carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

trainNumber.title: Train Number
trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

membershipPointsEarned.title: Membership Points Earned
membershipPointsEarned.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (E.g. stars, miles, etc.)

query.title: Query
query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

merchantReturnDays.title: Merchant Return Days
merchantReturnDays.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

director.title: Director
director.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

isAcceptingNewPatients.title: Is Accepting New Patients
isAcceptingNewPatients.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

occupationalCategory.title: Occupational Category
occupationalCategory.description:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

addOn.title: Add On
addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

identifier.title: Identifier
identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

usesDevice.title: Uses Device
usesDevice.description: Device used to perform the test.

inAlbum.title: In Album
inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

targetDescription.title: Target Description
targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

permissionType.title: Permission Type
permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

pagination.title: Pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

description.@value: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

mathExpression.title: Math Expression
mathExpression.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

albumProductionType.title: Album Production Type
albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

numberOfForwardGears.title: Number Of Forward Gears
numberOfForwardGears.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62

departureStation.title: Departure Station
departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

ticketedSeat.title: Ticketed Seat
ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

menuAddOn.title: Menu Add On
menuAddOn.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

recipeIngredient.title: Recipe Ingredient
recipeIngredient.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

fiberContent.title: Fiber Content
fiberContent.description: The number of grams of fiber.

industry.title: Industry
industry.description: The industry associated with the job position.

inLanguage.title: In Language
inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

employmentUnit.title: Employment Unit
employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

interactingDrug.title: Interacting Drug
interactingDrug.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

startDate.title: Start Date
startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

hasMenu.title: Has Menu
hasMenu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

dropoffTime.title: Dropoff Time
dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

artEdition.title: Art Edition
artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

publicAccess.title: Public Access
publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value

domiciledMortgage.title: Domiciled Mortgage
domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

geoTouches.title: Geo Touches
geoTouches.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

box.title: Box
box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

lender.title: Lender
lender.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

relatedStructure.title: Related Structure
relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

workload.title: Workload
workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

expertConsiderations.title: Expert Considerations
expertConsiderations.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

availableAtOrFrom.title: Available At Or From
availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

sportsActivityLocation.title: Sports Activity Location
sportsActivityLocation.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.title: News Updates And Guidelines
newsUpdatesAndGuidelines.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

partySize.title: Party Size
partySize.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

frequency.title: Frequency
frequency.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

alternativeOf.title: Alternative Of
alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

geoCoveredBy.title: Geo Covered By
geoCoveredBy.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

numberOfCredits.title: Number Of Credits
numberOfCredits.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

material.title: Material
material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

benefits.title: Benefits
benefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

propertyID.title: Property
propertyID.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

taxID.title: Tax
taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

hasCourseInstance.title: Has Course Instance
hasCourseInstance.description: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

priceCurrency.title: Price Currency
priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

restPeriods.title: Rest Periods
restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

billingIncrement.title: Billing Increment
billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

arrivalTerminal.title: Arrival Terminal
arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

energyEfficiencyScaleMax.title: Energy Efficiency Scale Max
energyEfficiencyScaleMax.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

reviewCount.title: Review Count
reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

area.title: Area
area.description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

defaultValue.title: Default Value
defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

browserRequirements.title: Browser Requirements
browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

predecessorOf.title: Predecessor Of
predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

callSign.title: Call Sign
