callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

flightNumber.title: Flight Number
flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.title: Cvd Num C19 Of Mech Vent Pats
cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

educationalFramework.title: Educational Framework
educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

legislationLegalForce.title: Legislation Legal Force
legislationLegalForce.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

partOfOrder.title: Part Of Order
partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

softwareAddOn.title: Software Add On
softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

aspect.title: Aspect
aspect.description: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

sender.title: Sender
sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.title: Health Plan Coinsurance Option
healthPlanCoinsuranceOption.description: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

serviceType.title: Service Type
serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

legislationResponsible.title: Legislation Responsible
legislationResponsible.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

legislationJurisdiction.title: Legislation Jurisdiction
legislationJurisdiction.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

description.@value: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

insertion.title: Insertion
insertion.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

engineDisplacement.title: Engine Displacement
engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

hasDeliveryMethod.title: Has Delivery Method
hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

mediaItemAppearance.title: Media Item Appearance
mediaItemAppearance.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

instructor.title: Instructor
instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

offers.title: Offers
offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

trainingSalary.title: Training Salary
trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

primaryImageOfPage.title: Primary Image Of Page
primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

subTest.title: Sub Test
subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

videoFrameSize.title: Video Frame Size
videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

boardingGroup.title: Boarding Group
boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

returnPolicyCountry.title: Return Policy Country
returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

image.title: Image
image.description: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

dateline.title: Dateline
dateline.description:
A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use [[contentLocation]].

Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

replacer.title: Replacer
replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

numberOfEpisodes.title: Number Of Episodes
numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

directors.title: Directors
directors.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

arrivalGate.title: Arrival Gate
arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

naics.title: Naics
naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

lyricist.title: Lyricist
lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

endDate.title: End Date
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

location.title: Location
location.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

applicationStartDate.title: Application Start Date
applicationStartDate.description: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

suggestedAge.title: Suggested Age
suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

transcript.title: Transcript
transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

addressRegion.title: Address Region
addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

firstAppearance.title: First Appearance
firstAppearance.description: Indicates the first known occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

jobLocationType.title: Job Location Type
jobLocationType.description: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

vehicleConfiguration.title: Vehicle Configuration
vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

hasMenuItem.title: Has Menu Item
hasMenuItem.description: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

participant.title: Participant
participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

multipleValues.title: Multiple Values
multipleValues.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

maximumIntake.title: Maximum Intake
maximumIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

musicArrangement.title: Music Arrangement
musicArrangement.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

pageStart.title: Page Start
pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

risks.title: Risks
risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

tongueWeight.title: Tongue Weight
tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

eligibleCustomerType.title: Eligible Customer Type
eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

hasPart.title: Has Part
hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

numberOfEmployees.title: Number Of Employees
numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

productGroupID.title: Product Group
productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

recommendedIntake.title: Recommended Intake
recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

itemListElement.title: Item List Element
itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

gtin13.title: Gtin13
gtin13.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

suggestedMaxAge.title: Suggested Max Age
suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

hasDriveThroughService.title: Has Drive Through Service
hasDriveThroughService.description: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

responsibilities.title: Responsibilities
responsibilities.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

serialNumber.title: Serial Number
serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

directApply.title: Direct Apply
directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specified job, navigating directly from the JobPosting url(s) supplied.

dateIssued.title: Date Issued
dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

specialOpeningHoursSpecification.title: Special Opening Hours Specification
specialOpeningHoursSpecification.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

accelerationTime.title: Acceleration Time
accelerationTime.description:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

minValue.title: Min Value
minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

quest.title: Quest
quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

recipeCategory.title: Recipe Category
recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipe—for example, appetizer, entree, etc.

seatingCapacity.title: Seating Capacity
seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons

episodeNumber.title: Episode Number
episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

toRecipient.title: To Recipient
toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

mediaAuthenticityCategory.title: Media Authenticity Category
mediaAuthenticityCategory.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

relatedCondition.title: Related Condition
relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

cvdNumICUBedsOcc.title: Cvd Num Icu Beds Occ
cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

codeRepository.title: Code Repository
codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

rsvpResponse.title: Rsvp Response
rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

sourceOrganization.title: Source Organization
sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

sku.title: Sku
sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

orderItemNumber.title: Order Item Number
orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

speechToTextMarkup.title: Speech To Text Markup
speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

gettingTestedInfo.title: Getting Tested Info
gettingTestedInfo.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

deathPlace.title: Death Place
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

additionalType.title: Additional Type
additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

eduQuestionType.title: Edu Question Type
eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

geoContains.title: Geo Contains
geoContains.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

identifyingTest.title: Identifying Test
identifyingTest.description: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

minimumPaymentDue.title: Minimum Payment Due
minimumPaymentDue.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

alumniOf.title: Alumni Of
alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

acceptedPaymentMethod.title: Accepted Payment Method
acceptedPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

usesHealthPlanIdStandard.title: Uses Health Plan Id Standard
usesHealthPlanIdStandard.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

sponsor.title: Sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

availableDeliveryMethod.title: Available Delivery Method
availableDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

hasCategoryCode.title: Has Category Code
hasCategoryCode.description: A Category code contained in this code set.

downloadUrl.title: Download Url
downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

availableFrom.title: Available From
availableFrom.description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

isUnlabelledFallback.title: Is Unlabelled Fallback
isUnlabelledFallback.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

incentives.title: Incentives
incentives.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

mechanismOfAction.title: Mechanism Of Action
mechanismOfAction.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

yearBuilt.title: Year Built
yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

playMode.title: Play Mode
playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

artworkSurface.title: Artwork Surface
artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

spokenByCharacter.title: Spoken By Character
spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

coach.title: Coach
coach.description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

diagram.title: Diagram
diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

stage.title: Stage
stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

character.title: Character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.
